tip.text: Closest thing to old school Italian in Park Slope. Pasta dishes rocked w/ large portions. We loved the Penne Rustico & anything w/ their homemade tomato sauce. Need to try the pizza, parm & meatballs

How does one leave a tip? You can't go wrong with anything on the menu. Try the fatoush, califlower & musakhan. All authentic dishes & large portions! A bit loud at the venue but food will compensate!
Seabass on drunken noodle, mango sticky rice and the service is nothing but smiles with a friendly tone

tip.text: Helena & the people talk about the buffalo wings yo!
$45 for the Omakase - 9 piece sushi + hand roll. Come here soon before you can't get a reservation!!
Late night craving for a milkshake? Try the vanilla & chocolate!
Sausage, whole egg, spinach biscuit for $8.50..satisfying!
Not my usual sandwich pick but the Roast Beef rocked! The Serano was good but the fig spread was overpowering. Huge portion. And...Zapps chips!
Fatty brisket, pulled pork, ribs and classic mac & cheese!
Shio ramen, I really want to like you but you were too salty for me :(
8 pieces of fresh cut bacon for $7.00..worth it!
I loved both the Salmon and Tuna Hako! Can't go wrong with any of the Hako.
$7 vegetarian, $8 chicken, $9 lamb lunch boxes. Generous portions with 2 sides, rice & naan. Loved the spicy Chicken Tikka Masala..meat was so tender and Eggplant Peas.
Still thinking about the jerk chicken and oxtail. Meat is oh so tender! Dining upstairs is def an experience. BYOB!
